#include <stdio.h>
int fib(int n);
void main(void)
{ int num, x = 6;
num = fib(x);
printf("num=%d\n", num);
}
int fib(int n)
{ if (n == 0 || n == 1)
return n;
else
return fib(n-2) + fib(n-1);
}
```

(7%) The following is a piece of code written by a programming language in an asynchronous way, what is the output order of A, B, and C? (Assuming that fs.readFile and fs.writeFile are I/O operations and take relative longer time to complete than other operations)
```javascript
const fs = require('fs');

let john = {
  id: 1031,
  name: "John",
  age: 18
};
fs.writeFile('john.json', JSON.stringify(john), function() {
  console.log('A');
fs.readFile('john.json', function(data) {
    console.log('B');
  });
});
console.log('C');
```

